parameters:
\n<Mage>Good day. Are you also staying at this inn? I stopped by on
my journey, and this has been the most wonderful lodging
I've found.

\n<Mage>There's even a little hot spring in the back. It's not
natural, but a healing mage has dissolved magical power into
it, so your skin will be glowing

\n<Mage>The food was also exquisite, with a focus on quality
ingredients. The bed was like sleeping on a cloud, it even
gave a sense of floating.

\n<Rui>...(This person isn't bad at all. Yet, I'm getting the urge
to scratch them.)

\n<Mage>Good day. Are you also staying at this inn? I stopped by on
my journey, and it turned out to be the most charming
lodging I've found.

\n<Mage>There's even a little hot spring in the back. It's not
natural, but a healing mage has dissolved magical power into
it, so it leaves your skin glowing

\n<Mage>The cuisine was also exquisite, with a focus on quality
ingredients. The bed was like sleeping on a cloud, giving
you a sense of floating.

\n<Rui>...(This person isn't bad at all. Yet, I'm getting the urge
to scratch them.)

\n<Adventurer A>Oh, it's you from that time! How are you? Are you here on
business today?

\n<Adventurer A>The security job for the phantom thief before was easy,
wasn't it? After all, we just stood around, and we got paid
as usual.

\n<Adventurer A>After that, the captain of the guards got a severe scolding.
That's definitely a demotion.
\n<Adventurer A>Hey, Rui... that was your name, right? How are you doing?

\n<Adventurer A>Ever since then, there's been something odd about Count
Noblesse. It seems like he's preparing for something big. A
lot of large carriages have been passing through.

\n<Adventurer A>Well, it's not really any of my business. I'm an adventurer,
after all. Non-interference in domestic affairs outside of
work is my principle. I just want to live as I please.

This is the entrance to the Rumare Guild. It doesn't smell
as much of alcohol compared to downstairs... I should have
registered here.
\n<Count Noblesse>...

\n<Lumare Guard A>Currently, a horde of monsters is attacking Driane! The
number appears to be considerable! It seems that many
powerful high-ranking monsters are included as well!

\n<Lumare Guard B>At this rate, Driane will...!! Shouldn't we go to support
them?

\n<Count Noblesse>Wait! You must not go!! Our top priority is to protect
Lumare! What will we do if the monsters attack here?

\n<Commander>Unfortunately, there is only one ladder. Even if we go down
to help, the number of people who can do so is limited.

\n<Commander>Furthermore, if that ladder is destroyed, those who went
down to help won't be able to return. A wise monster would
undoubtedly target the ladder.

\n<Commander>Also, considering the current situation where we don't know
when flying monsters might head this way... we cannot afford
to reduce our defenses here.
\n<Lumare Guard B>But at this rate...!! Is there nothing we can do...!?

\n<Count Noblesse>It's cruel, but... everyone is already doing their utmost to
protect themselves. All we can do is pray for their brave
fight.

\n<Commander>Fortunately, the only types of flying monsters currently
seen among them are imps and succubi. Even if they come this
way, they will be easy to deal with.

\n<Commander>However, this attack feels like it's being carried out with
some sort of intent. We should also consider the possibility
of reinforcements from the monsters in the future.

\n<Commander>For the sake of preparedness in case of an emergency, I will
share a desperate measure! What I am about to tell you must
not be disclosed to anyone, including the townspeople! You
will be subject to severe punishment if you do! Understood?

A lodging so comfortable that you look forward to going to
bed, and with a breakfast so delicious that you look forward
to waking up! Please enjoy your stay and check in at the
reception desk

\n<Rui>...(A bed you can't sleep in, and a breakfast so awful it's
made by an old lady. It's a far cry from the inn below.)

This is the entrance to the Rumare Guild. It doesn't smell
as much of alcohol compared to downstairs... I should have
registered here.

\n<Mage>Greetings. Are you also staying at this inn? I stopped by
during my travels, and it turned out to be the most charming
lodging I've encountered.

\n<Mage>There's even a little hot spring in the back. It's not
natural, but a healing mage has dissolved magical power into
it, so it leaves your skin glowing

\n<Mage>The cuisine was also exquisite, with a focus on quality
ingredients. The beds felt like sleeping on clouds, they
even gave a sense of floating.

\n<Rui>...(This person isn't bad at all. Yet, I'm getting the urge
to scratch them.)

\n<Soldier>Are you an adventurer from below? You may pass. Adventurers
are treated as "those who belong nowhere." Basically, if
there's a request, you can enter anywhere.

\n<Soldier>But that also means "you always have no allies." If there's
any inconvenience, we, the guards of Lumare, will thoroughly
eliminate you. Understood?

\n<Adventurer C>"The thief was too fast; I couldn't do anything... Maybe I
need to train to increase my casting speed. Sacrifice
firepower for burst strength..."

\n<Adventurer C>"No, that won't do. I've always been bad at physical
activities. I can only take my time to charge up and
release."

\n<Adventurer C>"It seems the Noblesse Earl is gathering magicians. I wonder
what he's planning this time. I've been invited too, but
something smells fishy, so I'll pass."

\n<Adventurer C>"I'm planning to leave this town soon. It's pretty here, but
I prefer towns with the smell of oil and such. Maybe I'll
head to Emberland."

\n<Heavily Armored Adventurer>Rumors of a cat beastman adventurer...? Ah, I know of them.
They're twins, right?

\n<Heavily Armored Adventurer>Oh, that's you? Anyone else? Hmm... sorry, I can't think of
anyone.

\n<Longsword Adventurer>A strong cat beast-person...? Hmm, I do have someone in
mind, but... they're not an adventurer.

\n<Longsword Adventurer>There were rumors about a cat beast-person causing a ruckus
around the Oregano area. They were so out of control that a
subjugation request was even issued.

\n<Longsword Adventurer>They were shouting "Come out, strong ones!" while snapping
trees and beating up adventurers, causing quite a commotion.
I don't know if that situation was ever resolved.

\n<Rui>A subjugation request, huh? Mmm, that doesn't sound like my
sister. Thanks!

\n<Rui>Ah, that must be someone else then. Thank you very much.
(Please, let it be someone else!)
\n<Longsword Adventurer>I hope you find your sister.
